         71-67=4 points per swing.  Certainly no big deal, but then again, that means the pet is TWO LEVELS LOWER, meaning less attack, less defense, less hp, less skills overall.</P><P>This is an interesting trade off - if it goes through like this, I retract my earlier statement about it being a nerf.  Rather, I think it is neither a nerf nor a buff.  It is NOT a great change, but not a bad one either.  It simply appeases one side of the crowd (those who didn't really care what they summoned and so now they're happy they always summon a dark blue) while punishing the other side (those who always resummoned to get the best pet).</P><P></P><P>Etadanik the Redeemed<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
