         When I first read about this change, I was thrilled, but after reading the reports coming in I'm a bit disappointed.  Haven't had a chance to test this myself as the patcher is taking forever (even on  cable) but I see no reason to doubt the information posted so far.</P><P>As far as some people's views on the highest summon pet not being important.</P><P>It's not just damage per swing, but damage averages being affected by the pet's level relative to the mob it's fighting.</P><P>A middle tier pet will also have fewer HPs, chances to resist and will take more damage during a fight vs the two higher summons.</P><P>When we had a possible 5 level variation in summons, there was a pretty good chance of getting one of the top 3 pet summons out of the possible five.  Now it's always the "middle" one (lowest of the top three), which is great for buddhism, but horrible for necromancers, magicians, enchanters... and does anyone know if shaman and shadowknights have been affected by this?</P><P>I'd almost rather have it the old way.</P><P>EDIT:  Made corrections and added info to make myself more clear.</P><P>Nakht Takharu - 58 Defiler - Conclave of the Damned - 7th Hammer</P><P></P><P>Edited by - Nakht on 07/24/2002  14:04:52</P><P>Edited by - Nakht on 07/24/2002  14:10:07<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
